DURBAN – The Newcastle Municipality has conveyed its condolences to the town’s newly elected mayor Xolani Dube following the death of his wife. Dube, a member of the IFP, was elected mayor following the local government elections in November last year. In a statement on Monday, the municipality extended its condolences after the death of Londiwe Dube. “The Newcastle Municipality, on behalf of all Newcastle residents, extends its heartfelt condolences to the first citizen of Newcastle mayor Xolani Dube  following the untimely passing of the town’s first lady, Londiwe Dube,” said the municipality. The municipality also wished Dube strength and courage during this difficult period. “The community also mourns with the Dube family and will remember the late first lady as someone who was passionately and unequivocally supportive of any good cause. May the late Mrs Dube’s legacy continue to echo throughout the ages,” the municipality said. Earlier this month, The Mercury  reported that Emalahleni Local Municipality mayor Linah Malatjie and her husband Esau Malatjie died tragically in hospital after they were involved in a head-on collision on the R544 between Gemsbokspruit and Verena in Mpumalanga. THE MERCURY